This paper discusses Constraint Programming (CP) and its application in solving problems, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the solver in a competition, which could be relevant to Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Machine Learning (cs.LG).
